<body>
    <h1>1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Introduction</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p></p>
<div class=3D"">
<div class=3D"childtabs-macro" data-fixed-position=3D"false">
<div class=3D"aui-tabs horizontal-tabs" data-aui-responsive=3D"true">
<strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data-conte=
nt-id=3D"1203279602">The API Odyssey</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"a754afe0-7384-4b32-acf3-e4bd6c8d=
0746-1203279602">
<div class=3D"sectionColumnWrapper">
<div class=3D"sectionMacro">
<div class=3D"sectionMacroRow">
<div class=3D"columnMacro" style=3D"width:80%;min-width:80%;max-width:80%;"=
>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">This video gives a brief outline of t=
he development lifecycle on the Westpac Mesh Platform. It will take you thr=
ough from developing your API from a swagger specification, building and de=
ploying your code, and then to a how a customer consumes your API.</span></=
p>
<p></p>
<div class=3D"embeddedObject">
<video src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279602/API Odessey.mp4" height=3D"3=
80" width=3D"80%" controls>
Your browser does not support the HTML5 video element
</video>
</div>
<p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"sectionMacro">
<div class=3D"sectionMacroRow">
<h2 id=3D"TheAPIOdyssey-Summaryofdevelopmentlifecycle"><strong>Summary of d=
evelopment lifecycle</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>The developer will receive a Swagger specification from his designer. T=
his is the contract that defines your API to consumers.</li>
<li>Using Westpac Mesh Developer tools, we can generate a stub Java project=
 from the swagger specification.</li>
<li>Write your code and unit tests!</li>
<li>Check the code into Bitbucket, our version control system.</li>
<li>This triggers the continuous integration pipeline in Bamboo, which comp=
iles and builds your code and runs your unit tests.</li>
<li>If the tests are successful, the API is loaded into a Docker container =
with Tomcat and Java installed.</li>
<li>The container is pushed to Artifactory, our binary repository manager.<=
/li>
<li>This triggers the continuous delivery pipeline in Bamboo, where the Doc=
ker container is loaded onto the platform.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"TheAPIOdyssey-SummaryofAPIconsumptionbyacustomer"><strong>Summary=
 of API consumption by a customer</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>APIs on the platform are exposed through Axway, our API gateway.</li>
<li>When a request is made, it is directed to NGINX, our load balancer.</li=
>
<li>When an API starts up it is registered in Consul, our service registry.=
</li>
<li>NGINX communicates with Consul to know which Docker container to redire=
ct the request to.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"TheAPIOdyssey-Importantpoints"><strong>Important points</strong><=
/h2>
<ul>
<li>Code generation saves time from writing boilerplate code and includes a=
ll the necessary helper libraries to run on the platform. Additionally, it =
ensures that the code has a direct mapping to the API contract.</li>
<li>You are free to use any IDE that suits your project.</li>
<li>Source check-ins to the master branch of a project will automatically t=
rigger a build and deployment into the Dev1 environment.</li>
<li>In the build pipeline, your unit (eg. Junit) tests are run.</li>
<li>In the deploy pipeline, your integration (eg. Newman/Postman) tests are=
 run.</li>
<li>Multiple instances of any single API can be running simultaneously.</li=
>
<li>The same Swagger specification that you develop from will be used by yo=
ur consumers.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279605">Roles and Responsibilties</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"a754afe0-7384-4b32-acf3-e4bd6c8d=
0746-1203279605">
<div class=3D"sectionColumnWrapper">
<div class=3D"sectionMacro">
<div class=3D"sectionMacroRow">
<div class=3D"columnMacro" style=3D"width:80%;min-width:80%;max-width:80%;"=
>
<h2 id=3D"RolesandResponsibilties-Overview"><strong>Overview</strong></h2>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"208" src=3D"8946eb3856717e73ba142892c2e8090560eaf6be2dfc38c106dd742355=
09a01c" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279605/image2022-9-20_1=
5-28-55.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663651735670&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1202995173" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2022-9-20_15-28-55.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279605" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"4" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"RolesandResponsibilties-YourroleasaWestpacMeshDeveloper"><strong>=
Your role as a Westpac Mesh Developer&nbsp;</strong></h2>
<p>The Designer will provide the Developer with the component contract whic=
h defines your API.</p>
<p>The Developer implements the contract by writing the code logic.</p>
<p>The Developer writes the unit tests and integration (idempotent) test ca=
ses and ensures they pass.</p>
<p>The Developer manages deployments to the platform, and performs PIV.</p>
<p>The Developer is responsible for managing security reviews with ISG.</p>
<p>The Developer is responsible for maintaining, supporting and troubleshoo=
ting their component.</p>
<p>Westpac Mesh is a platform to make it easier to build and run digital so=
lutions. You still own your API</p>
<p><br></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279607">Swagger Specification</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"a754afe0-7384-4b32-acf3-e4bd6c8d=
0746-1203279607">
<div class=3D"sectionColumnWrapper">
<div class=3D"sectionMacro">
<div class=3D"sectionMacroRow">
<div class=3D"columnMacro">
<h2 id=3D"SwaggerSpecification-HowwelldoyouknowSwagger?"><strong>How well d=
o you know </strong><strong>Swagger</strong><strong>?</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Swagger is the industry standard specification for RESTful webservices<=
/li>
<li>Forces contract-first development, we encourage project teams to genera=
te code from their Swagger specification</li>
<li>Westpac Mesh provides a pre-defined 'Golden template':&nbsp;<a href=3D"=
https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/contracts/browse/t=
emplates" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://bitbucket.srv.we=
stpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/contracts/browse/templates</a>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Consumable by all Westpac Mesh customers</li>
<li>The Swagger specification goes through a governance process and has to =
be digitally signed before deployment to higher environments</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"SwaggerSpecification-HowdoweuseSwaggerfromday1?"><strong>How do w=
e use </strong><strong>Swagger</strong><strong> from day 1?</strong></h2>
<p>We can simultaneously:</p>
<ul>
<li>Code</li>
<li>Test</li>
<li>Consume</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"SwaggerSpecification-MoreInformation"><strong>More Information</s=
trong></h2>
<p>More in-depth details for writing a Swagger specification and design sta=
ndards are given in the Westpac Mesh Designer Induction (search 'Mesh' in e=
Academy).</p>
<p>Westpac Mesh hosts a Swagger editor to allow you to easily edit a Swagge=
r:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://swagger.mesh.westpac.com.au/" class=3D"external-=
link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://swagger.mesh.westpac.com.au/</a></p>
<p>Click the below link to get more general information on the Swagger webs=
ite.</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://swagger.io/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"=
><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual=
-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image confluence-thumbnail" dragga=
ble=3D"false" height=3D"100" src=3D"dd5de5f9aba344ae12bad1682fbc60f6ea2b4d8=
a7f8bfc3ebda94ce016a035a7" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/12032796=
07/image2021-3-12_13-10-17.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D166357113=
6273&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource=
-id=3D"1203279608" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-=
type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-3-12_13=
-10-17.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-li=
nked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=
=3D"1203279607" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" alt=3D"" width=
=3D"264"></span></a></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p></p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
